import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='wheat', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the trend of wheat production over time?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    data_grouped = data.groupby('year').mean().reset_index()
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = sns.barplot(x='year', y='wheat', data=data_grouped, color='blue', label='Wheat')
    ax = sns.barplot(x='year', y='wages', data=data_grouped, color='orange', label='Wages')
    ax.legend()
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the average wheat production and wages per year?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
